    "question_id" : 53565210,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can do simple</p>\n\n<pre><code>super(a != null ? a.getName() : resolveNullA())\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>but the better solution would be to create the <code>Car</code> instance by using some implementation of <a href=\"https://www.tutorialspoint.com/design_pattern/factory_pattern.htm\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Factory</a> </p>\n\n<pre><code>public class VehicleFactory {\n    ...\n\n    public Car getCar(Car anotherCar) {\n        if(anotherCar != null) {\n            return new Car(anotherCar.getName()); \n        } else {\n            resolveNullAnotherCar();\n        }\n    }\n\n    ...\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
