    "creation_date" : 1758811484,
    "answer_id" : 79774983,
    "question_id" : 53565210,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>As of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Java_version_history#Java_SE_25_(LTS)\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Java 25</a>, released 2025-09, you can. See <a href=\"https://openjdk.org/jeps/513\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><em>JEP 513: Flexible Constructor Bodies</em></a>.</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>public class Car extends Vehicle {\n    public Car(Car a){\n        if (a == null) {\n            throw new IllegalArgumentException(&quot;Car is null&quot;);\n        } \n        super(a.getName());\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
